Text.string: The Children of the Vault are dangerous. Trust me, you don't want to see what happens if a bandit has the power of the Vaults.
The Vaults were built by aliens called Eridians. Then they vanished. Tannis can tell you more.
That map will lead us to Vaults all across the Borderlands. If the Children of the Vault want the map, that makes them the competition.
I've been with the Raiders a long time. A soldier named Roland started the group to fight against Handsome Jack.

Our old ship, Sanctuary, was attacked by an ex-Dahl soldier called Hector. Real prick, that one. He took our ship and tried to use the Vault Map to take over Pandora. Another Vault Hunter killed him. Then I destroyed Sanctuary to prevent a catastrophe. That's how we lost the map.
The Calypso Twins believe the map will lead them to something called the Great Vault. Never heard of it, but maybe Tannis knows more.
So... Tannis is a Siren. Sorry, wish I could've told you.
Great job thrashing that Agonizer thing.
Pain and Terror. What a pain in my ass.
Troy's dead. We finally avenged Maya, killer.
Can't believe Tyreen got away. Again.
We'll find Tyreen, and we'll stop her.
So, Ava's a Siren now. Gotta say, I didn't see that coming.
Heading to the fabled planet of Nekrotafeyo. What a trip.
Running and gunning with the First Vault Hunter. Can't believe he's still alive.
Typhon's... not quite what I expected.
Nekrotafeyo. I can't believe it's real.
Hope this Machine does what Typhon says it'll do. Otherwise, Pandora's screwed.
This thing had better work.
Great. More Maliwan troops, that's just great.
This is it. Time to stop Tyreen.
Let's end this, killer.
One last chance to save Pandora. You've got this.
We've lost so much. It's time to take the fight to Tyreen.
I spent my entire life hunting Vaults. To think that now the way to save the galaxy is to close one that never should have been opened.
Wherever the COV go, we'll be there to stop them.
S'up, killer?
Have you seen these Calypsos' ECHOcasts? They're out of their damn minds.
How you holdin' up? The fight can really take it out of ya, huh?
I know you can handle whatever we throw at you, you flaming badass, you.
I'm fine. Don't worry about me. Focus on the mission at hand.
Tyreen took my powers. It's like Tannis said. I'm no longer a Siren.
I've had... setbacks before, but not like this. Heh, I knew Pandora wouldn't let me leave without taking one last thing. Just didn't think it'd be... y'know.
Leave it to Ellie to scrap and salvage and fix up a ship in the middle of Pandora. Then again, I've seen her sitting in a rocking chair, picking off bandits for fun.
Thanks for getting Sanctuary running. You're worth your weight in Eridium.
We have to focus on the mission. Find the Vault on Promethea. Tyreen Calypso took my powers, but I'll die before she gets the power of a Vault.
The Crimson Raiders and Atlas. Look, it's a dangerous galaxy—I got a feeling we're gonna need all the help we can get.
Hope we made the right call with this Rhys guy.
Rhys really turned Atlas around. Hope we can help him fend off Maliwan.
Zer0 sure knows how to make an entrance.
Man... Maliwan and the COV, a match made in hell if I ever saw one. Sounds like their alliance has been in the making for months. Makes me think the Calypsos already knew about the Promethea Vault.
Can't even get away from the COV on Promethea.
It's good to have Maya onboard. She said you really kicked ass down there.
I see Maya hasn't slowed down a bit. Still a total badass.
Ava's quite the little firecracker, huh? In a completely unrelated note, some gear from the bridge is missing.
Katagawa. What a lunatic. I'm starting to think you have to be an egomaniac to become a corporation CEO.
It's time to open the Vault. Be ready for the Calypsos, killer. You know they're coming.
Heard you gave Katagawa one serious ass-kicking. Good. Maliwan tore that city to shreds. Gonna take a long time to rebuild, but I think Rhys is up to the challenge. Maybe.
The Promethean Vault... been a while since we opened one. If memory serves, there's gonna be a monster, loot, and a surprise. The Eridians love surprises.
Man, Ava does not want to be left on this ship. I admire the fire, but a Vault is no place for kids.
We'll hold down the fort. Find the Vault. And be careful.
About Maya... yeah, I don't know. Wound's still too fresh, but... we have to keep moving.
She's... really gone. But there's no time to mourn. If we don't stop the Calypsos from opening another Vault, they might be too powerful to—No, one step at a time.
Ava blames herself. And I get it—when Handsome Jack killed Roland, I didn't sleep for a week. If only I'd reacted quicker, I might have saved him.
Me and Maya go back a long time. She saved my ass too many times to count. And she was a good friend.

Eden-6. People call it a paradise planet, and home to Jakobs Corporation. I'm just hoping they're friendly. Everywhere they go, the Calypsos attract more and more followers. We could use another ally.
Hammerlock, Brick, Tina, and Mordecai. The old gang's back together! Just in time—we're gonna need them in the fight.
I always heard Eden-6 was a paradise.
Glad we were able to break Hammerlock out of that place.
Looks like no one's safe from the COV. Something tells me that Tyreen Calypso knew about these Vaults a long time before she found the map. Wonder how.
Wainwright Jakobs. From what I can tell, he was supposed to become the next CEO after his father died—but then the corporation was bought out.
Wainwright said you “lit the bonfires of the resistance”. I'm guessing that means taking down the COV and acting like a badass. Wish I could be down there fighting with you.
Looking forward to proving Aurelia wrong.
I like this Clay guy. He knows how to get it done.
All else aside, that's a hell of a mansion they've got there.
S'up, smooth operator? Clay says you're Rogue material, whatever that means.
Vive la résistance, and all that.
Good work down there on Eden-6.
Tannis. We have to find Tannis.
Glad Aurelia won't be a problem anymore.
We already lost Maya. We can't lose Tannis, too.
Guess we're heading home to Pandora.
Children of the Vault. Can't believe the bandits actually stopped fighting amongst themselves.
I should've seen the COV coming.
Can't believe Maya's gone.
Good to have Hammerlock back on the team.
I knew Aurelia was gonna be trouble.
Glad to have Clay on the team. Seems pretty capable.
BALEX is... interesting company, but I guess we can't get rid of him.
Been trudging around in Eden's dirty underbelly, huh?
We're going to get Tannis back.
Carnivora... never seen anything like that.
Looked like you were havin' some fun out there with Vaughn.
Troy's dead. One down, one to go.
Typhon seems pretty glad to have some company.
Gotta get that Machine up and running.
Typhon's gone... he'll live on in stories, I guess.
Strange times...
There used to be so many of us on Pandora... now it's like we're spilled across the stars.
We can't stop now. There's too much to do.
It's not over yet.
Glad to have so many badasses on our side.
More Sirens... why do we all end up on Pandora?
I'll be fine. Eyes on the prize, killer.
Guess this is home, now.
The Crimson Raiders are bringing the fight to Promethea. Roland would be proud.
Always wanted to go to Athenas. Never found the time.
Nice work up there, killer.
There's Katagawa's killer.
Got a mission for ya, killer.
Got somethin' for ya.
You busy?
S'up, killer?
Yo, Vault Hunter.
Hey.
How's it goin' out there?
You win the war for us yet?
Another lovely day, huh?
There's always another ass to kick.
No rest for... well, for any of us.
We'll make it through this.
Got a mission for ya.
Ready for a job?
The Raiders need you.
Got a thing for you to do.
New mission for you.
Finish that mission yet?
How's that thing goin'?
You handling that mission?
Taking care of that job I asked you to do?
I know you're out there kickin' ass.
Later.
Later, killer.
See ya.
All right, we'll talk later.
Yep, later.
Get back out there, killer.
Go kick some ass, huh?
Make 'em hurt, killer.
We'll catch up later.
Raise some hell, Vault Hunter.
